title: [ONNX] Cannot export upsample op
body_html:
My model contains a 2D upsample op
nn.Upsample(scale_factor=4, mode='bilinear')

But it cannot be exported to ONNX

  • PyTorch or Caffe2: Pytorch
  • OS: Ubuntu 16.01
  • PyTorch version: 0.4.0a0+f8270c0
  • How you installed PyTorch (conda, pip, source): conda
  • Python version: 3.6.4

torch.onnx.export(self, [input_var], os.path.join(output_path, "model.onnx"), output_names=output_names)
1070 File "/lib/python3.6/site-packages/torch/onnx/init.py", line 12, in export
1071 return utils.export(*args, **kwargs)
1072 File "/lib/python3.6/site-packages/torch/onnx/utils.py", line 83, in export
1073 _export(model, args, f, export_params, verbose, training, input_names, output_names)
1074 File "/lib/python3.6/site-packages/torch/onnx/utils.py", line 138, in _export
1075 _optimize_trace(trace, aten)
1076 File "/lib/python3.6/site-packages/torch/onnx/utils.py", line 94, in _optimize_trace
1077 torch._C._jit_pass_onnx(trace, aten)
1078 File "/lib/python3.6/site-packages/torch/onnx/init.py", line 27, in _run_symbolic_function
1079 return utils._run_symbolic_function(*args, **kwargs)
1080 File "/lib/python3.6/site-packages/torch/onnx/utils.py", line 333, in _run_symbolic_function
1081 return fn(g, *inputs, **attrs)
1082 TypeError: upsample_bilinear2d() got an unexpected keyword argument 'align_corners' (occurred when translating upsample_bilinear2d)
